# myClawTeam Architecture Plan

## Product Context

The issues define a static Astro landing page for myClawTeam. The core positioning is "Agent Team for Founders" with the hero line "You just talk, we handle the rest." No `PRODUCT.md` is present in this checkout, so issue copy is the source of truth for brand and messaging.

## Module Structure

- `package.json`: npm scripts for `dev`, `build`, `preview`, and later `test:e2e`.
- `astro.config.mjs`: Astro configuration, Tailwind integration, sitemap integration, and site URL handling.
- `tsconfig.json`: strict TypeScript settings using Astro's recommended base.
- `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`: shared HTML shell, global metadata defaults, canonical/OG/Twitter tags, favicon/asset links, fonts, and global stylesheet import.
- `src/pages/index.astro`: page composition only; imports the layout and section components in final landing-page order.
- `src/components/sections/`: landing-page sections:
  - `Hero.astro`
  - `ValueProps.astro`
  - `HowItWorks.astro`
  - `FeatureHighlights.astro`
  - `FinalCta.astro`
  - `Footer.astro`
- `src/content/site.ts`: shared site metadata and landing-page copy constants used by layout, sections, JSON-LD, and tests.
- `src/styles/global.css`: Tailwind directives, base element styles, CSS variables/tokens that should not live directly in component classes.
- `public/`: static assets including `favicon.svg`, logo/brand mark, `og-image.png`, and `robots.txt`.
- `.env.example`: documented build-time variables such as `PUBLIC_SITE_URL`.
- `tests/e2e/`: Playwright smoke tests once the assembled page exists.

## Shared Types and Data

- Keep shared constants in `src/content/site.ts` so copy and SEO metadata are not duplicated across components and tests.
- Use a small typed metadata shape for layout props, for example title, description, canonical path, ogImage, and JSON-LD data.
- Prefer static Astro components for sections. Do not introduce client-side JavaScript unless a later issue explicitly requires interactivity.

## Issue Dependencies

- Issue #1 initializes the Astro/TypeScript base and unlocks all implementation work.
- Issue #2 depends on #1 and establishes Tailwind tokens/global styles used by all visual components.
- Issue #3 depends on #1 and creates `BaseLayout`, robots, sitemap, and SEO defaults.
- Issues #4 and #5 depend on the base project/layout and provide env URL wiring and public assets.
- Issues #6 through #11 depend on the initialized project and should use shared copy/tokens established by #2 and `site.ts`.
- Issue #12 depends on all section components (#6-#11) and composes `index.astro`.
- Issue #13 depends on the layout/page assembly and adds final page metadata plus JSON-LD Organization schema.
- Issue #14 depends on assembled sections and performs responsive polish across breakpoints.
- Issue #15 depends on the app being assembled and configures Playwright against `astro preview`.
- Issue #16 depends on env/build readiness and validates production output plus Lighthouse baseline.
- Issue #17 depends on env documentation and final build behavior, then documents self-hosting deployment.

## Key Design Decisions

- Build as a static Astro site to keep the page fast, cacheable, and easy to self-host from `dist/`.
- Use Tailwind for layout and component styling, backed by a minimal custom theme for myClawTeam colors, typography, spacing, and focus states.
- Keep content data centralized and typed. This reduces drift between SEO metadata, section copy, tests, and future README instructions.
- Treat `PUBLIC_SITE_URL` as the canonical origin for sitemap, canonical URLs, and social metadata, with a safe local fallback for development.
- Use semantic section markup, accessible buttons/links, visible focus styles, responsive grid/stack layouts, and no horizontal scrolling on mobile.
- Ship mostly static HTML/CSS. Avoid framework client hydration unless a future requirement needs it.
- Keep Playwright smoke tests focused on production-like behavior: built site preview, hero text, CTA presence/clickability, metadata, and console cleanliness.
